<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 04 at 6:24PM EDT until April 04 at 6:45PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 645 PM EDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN ALLEGAN COUNTY...
At 623 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 6 miles north of
Allegan, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Allegan...             Wayland...             Dorr...
Hopkins...             Burnips...             Green Lake...
Bradley...             Shelbyville...         Allegan Municipal Ai...
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
